12:35.220 --> 12:36.847
My client has made
the choice not to have...
No. No.

12:36.890 --> 12:39.108
...an abortion.
You don't get to use
the word "choice."

12:39.150 --> 12:40.185
That fetus
is wholly

12:40.220 --> 12:41.448
my clients'
genetic material:

12:41.490 --> 12:43.355
their egg,
their sperm.

12:43.390 --> 12:45.051
The only one who
gets to choose

12:45.090 --> 12:46.455
is the actual mother.

12:46.490 --> 12:47.491
We would disagree.
Ah.

12:47.530 --> 12:48.827
And that settles
that, then?

12:48.860 --> 12:50.122
We're suing.

12:50.170 --> 12:52.161
Today.

12:52.200 --> 12:55.192
W-Wha... you're
suing for what?

12:55.240 --> 12:56.389
To force my client
to have an abortion?

12:56.440 --> 12:58.135
How does
that work?
Economic
devastation.

12:58.170 --> 13:00.502
Your client
breached her contract.

13:00.540 --> 13:02.201
The Isenstadts put
over half a million

13:02.240 --> 13:03.377
into this
surrogacy.
Oh, come on.

13:03.410 --> 13:04.570
Searching for
a surrogate,

13:04.610 --> 13:08.046
fertility fees,
Tara's weekly payments.

13:08.080 --> 13:09.547
A half million is going
to bankrupt your client.

13:09.580 --> 13:11.514
Unless she
decides to honor

13:11.550 --> 13:13.154
the terms
of her contract.

13:13.190 --> 13:14.157
Wow.

13:14.190 --> 13:15.179
Then _we'll see
you in court.

13:15.220 --> 13:17.085
No, I won't be
seeing you anywhere.

13:17.130 --> 13:18.085
You're fired.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.348
The Isenstadts
are terminating

13:20.400 --> 13:22.095
your employment
as Tara's lavwer.

13:22.130 --> 13:23.267
Well, they
can't do that

13:23.300 --> 13:24.324
until the surrogacy
is concluded.

13:24.370 --> 13:26.065
No, they can't
do that

13:26.100 --> 13:27.431
until the contract
is concluded,

13:27.470 --> 13:30.109
and you've decided
the contract is concluded.

13:30.140 --> 13:33.177
So unless you're into
doing this case pro bono,

13:33.210 --> 13:34.370
it was nice
meeting you.

13:42.620 --> 13:44.815
(Will and Diane arguing)

13:49.290 --> 13:50.985
WILL:
Not in this context.

13:51.030 --> 13:51.985
DIANE:_
Are you serious?

13:52.030 --> 13:52.894
You put your interests

13:52.930 --> 13:54.227
over the interests
of the firm, Diane.

13:54.260 --> 13:55.227
This is my firm!

13:55.260 --> 13:56.352
It was your firm.

13:56.400 --> 13:57.367
Then get
the security guards.

13:57.400 --> 13:58.958
Carry me out.
No.

13:59.000 --> 14:00.365
We have enough
respect for you

14:00.400 --> 14:01.992
not to make this
a public spectacle.

14:08.910 --> 14:11.447
You want to end
it this way?

14:11.480 --> 14:13.448
Diane,
you ended it.

14:13.480 --> 14:15.539
Now, go be
a judge.

14:15.580 --> 14:17.582
We have work
to do here.

14:43.110 --> 14:44.077
(phone ringing)
Hello.

14:44.110 --> 14:45.077
BOY:
Is Grace there?

14:45.110 --> 14:47.578
No, this is her mother.
May I ask who's calling?

14:47.620 --> 14:48.575
Jimmy Lawrence.

14:48.620 --> 14:49.518
She should be back in an hour.

14:49.550 --> 14:51.381
What is this regarding?

14:51.420 --> 14:52.546
Was that
for me?

14:52.590 --> 14:53.557
No, Grace.

14:53.590 --> 14:55.319
Who's Jimmy Lawrence?

14:55.360 --> 14:56.918
Someone from school.

14:56.960 --> 14:57.949
Why?

14:57.990 --> 14:59.992
Well, he was
calling for Grace.

15:04.500 --> 15:05.467
Zach, is something

15:05.500 --> 15:08.298
going on with
your sister?

15:08.340 --> 15:09.432
No.

15:09.470 --> 15:11.461
But something's
going on?

15:13.340 --> 15:15.501
Zach, what?

15:15.540 --> 15:17.246
Grace has nothing
to do with this, Mom.

15:17.280 --> 15:18.269
It's... it's not her.

15:20.550 --> 15:21.539
(sighs)

15:36.760 --> 15:39.092
But Grace...

15:39.130 --> 15:40.097
I don't understand.

15:40.140 --> 15:41.129
Where...?

15:44.240 --> 15:46.561
So that's why
this kid is calling?

15:46.610 --> 15:48.271
Lots of kids.

15:51.780 --> 15:53.270
ELI:
We want you back, Marilyn.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.641
PETER:
Yes, I thought that we were

15:55.680 --> 15:56.988
a bit hasty in moving you

15:57.020 --> 15:57.941
to the Transit Authority Board.

15:57.990 --> 15:59.742
Promoting me to the Transit
Authority Board.

15:59.790 --> 16:01.655
PETER:
Yes, well,

16:01.690 --> 16:03.351
we heard you weren't
very happy there.

16:03.390 --> 16:05.654
Yeah, I didn't
feel... qualified.
Then come back to us.

16:05.690 --> 16:07.624
We're reorganizing
the ethics commission,

16:07.660 --> 16:09.150
giving it more power.

16:09.200 --> 16:10.622
We'd like you
to head it up.

16:10.670 --> 16:14.561
PETER: And we'd like
to announce today.

16:14.600 --> 16:16.033
In what way, reorganizing?

16:16.070 --> 16:17.765
Well, the ethics commission

16:17.810 --> 16:19.698
has always seemed isolated
here in Chicago.

16:19.740 --> 16:22.629
We want to move your offices
into the governor's suite

16:22.680 --> 16:24.545
in Springfield--
more in the...

16:24.580 --> 16:25.740
heat of the action.

16:31.650 --> 16:33.186
No, thank you.

16:33.220 --> 16:34.778
Wait a minute.
Wait, whoa, whoa.

16:34.820 --> 16:36.583
Why not?

16:36.620 --> 16:40.158
Pat Quinn governed
from Springfield.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.418
Rod Blagojevich
governed from Chicago.

16:42.460 --> 16:44.269
Each governor is different.

16:44.300 --> 16:45.790
Where are you gonna
be, Mr. Florrick?

16:45.830 --> 16:48.731
ELI: Oh, he'll be both
here and Springfield.

16:48.770 --> 16:50.738
Then why are you adding
all the offices here?

16:53.580 --> 16:56.674
I'll be in Chicago.
And you want the
ethics offices

16:56.710 --> 16:59.577
isolated out in Springfield?

16:59.610 --> 17:01.077
No, thank you.

17:01.120 --> 17:02.712
What if the offices were here?

17:02.750 --> 17:05.787
Along with unfettered access--
yes, I'd consider it.

17:05.820 --> 17:07.685
(chuckles):
No one gets unfettered access.

17:07.720 --> 17:10.154
Give us a clay to think about it.

17:10.190 --> 17:13.353
Okay?
Thank you, Mr. Florrick.

17:16.300 --> 17:17.722
They hate me, don't they?
No, I don't think

17:17.770 --> 17:18.794
they hate you.

17:18.830 --> 17:20.764
They want you to consider
all the repercussions.

17:20.800 --> 17:23.735
And they can do that?
Take all my money?

17:23.770 --> 17:25.499
I don't even have that much.
Well, you have

17:25.540 --> 17:27.701
the $120,000 coming
from your parents' trust

17:27.740 --> 17:29.139
when you turn 21.

17:29.180 --> 17:31.478
They can take that.

17:32.310 --> 17:34.141
Excuse me one second, Tara.

17:35.720 --> 17:38.541
Is that her?
Is that the surrogate?

17:38.590 --> 17:42.287
Yes. Look, David, I'm doing this
pro bono, one of mine.

17:42.320 --> 17:44.459
I will not exceed
30 billable...
I'm taking first chair with you.

17:44.490 --> 17:46.321
You're what?
Tara?

17:46.360 --> 17:49.796
Hi. I'm David Lee.

17:49.830 --> 17:52.162
I am in awe of your courage,

17:52.200 --> 17:54.395
young lady.
Life is such
(laughs)

17:54.440 --> 17:57.637
a precious commodity...
isn't it?

18:00.910 --> 18:02.275
What are you on?

18:02.310 --> 18:04.369
Something for Will.

18:04.410 --> 18:06.776
I need you to...
No, come to think of it,

18:06.810 --> 18:07.845
you're still friends with Cary

18:07.880 --> 18:09.416
and the fourth years,
aren't you?

18:09.450 --> 18:11.645
What do you
need, David?

18:11.690 --> 18:14.284
No, that's okay.

18:14.320 --> 18:16.788
Robyn, I want you to look
into this Dr. Tuft...

18:16.820 --> 18:19.789
ALICIA
And you've been seeing

18:19.830 --> 18:21.798
Tara Bach
for how long?

18:21.830 --> 18:24.196
I've been her ob-gyn
for about seven months now.

18:24.230 --> 18:25.891
I see. And when
is she due?

18:25.930 --> 18:27.830
In approximately 12 weeks.

18:27.870 --> 18:29.861
ALICIA: And in your
professional opinion,

18:29.900 --> 18:32.232
is Tara's fetus viable?
Objection, Your Honor.
Relevance.

18:32.270 --> 18:33.806
This is
a breach of contract suit.

18:33.840 --> 18:35.774
Well, let's find out the
relevance. What's the relevance,

18:35.810 --> 18:38.404
Counselor? _
If Tara's fetus is Viable,
Your Honor,

18:38.450 --> 18:40.771
then she can't abort, and there
is no breach of contract.

18:40.820 --> 18:42.811
JUDGE: Well, that makes
sense to me, Counselor.

18:42.850 --> 18:43.817
No further questions.

18:43.850 --> 18:45.738
Just a few more
for the defense.

18:45.790 --> 18:46.814
Thank you, Alicia.

18:46.850 --> 18:48.408
What...

18:48.460 --> 18:49.757
(clears throat softly)

18:49.790 --> 18:52.179
Why was the amnio
performed so late

18:52.230 --> 18:54.528
in the pregnancy, Doctor?
Why?

18:54.560 --> 18:56.289
Uh, I-I didn't perform it.
I know.

18:56.330 --> 18:57.592
Dr. Tuft did.

18:57.630 --> 18:59.791
But do you know why
the amnio was performed

18:59.830 --> 19:01.195
so late _in the
second trimester?

19:01.240 --> 19:02.593
DOCTOR: Well, this was
the second amnio.

19:02.640 --> 19:05.165
The first was performed
in April.

19:05.210 --> 19:06.563
DAVID: And did
you find that

19:06.610 --> 19:08.430
Tara had spotting
after the first amnio?

19:08.480 --> 19:09.902
Yes.
And could this
have come

19:09.940 --> 19:11.578
from a poorly
performed amnio?

19:11.610 --> 19:13.817
JUDGE: Okay, let's hold up here.
I'm not sure why

19:13.850 --> 19:15.875
the plaintiff isn't objecting,

19:15.920 --> 19:18.218
but what is
the relevance?
Pure curi05ity, Your Honor.

19:18.250 --> 19:19.808
Well, let's satisfy
our curiosity

19:19.850 --> 19:21.750
on our own time, shall we?

19:21.790 --> 19:26.227
I sustain the objection
that never came.

19:26.260 --> 19:28.956
(sighs) So, you want
to sue the hospital.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.468
I don't want to;
I will sue the hospital.

19:31.500 --> 19:33.730
Their amnio caused
these birth defects.

19:33.770 --> 19:35.635
And you want
the child born?

19:35.670 --> 19:37.831
No. Your client wants
the child born.

19:37.870 --> 19:41.203
Yes, but it means more to a suit
if the child is born?

19:41.240 --> 19:43.208
(chuckles)
$8 million more.

19:43.250 --> 19:44.706
It's pain
and suffering.

19:44.750 --> 19:47.844
$2 million if Tara aborts,
$10 million if she doesn't.

19:47.880 --> 19:49.848
Does Tara know that?

19:49.880 --> 19:51.689
What, that we're suing?

19:51.720 --> 19:54.712
No. She's doing it
because she believes it.

19:54.760 --> 19:56.489
HOWARD:
I'm pro-choice.

19:56.520 --> 19:58.556
It gives you the most options.

19:58.590 --> 20:00.797
HECT: Abortion is a sin.
DAVID: You're a Republican;
you have to say that.

20:00.830 --> 20:01.854
HECT: No, I'm
not a Republican.

20:01.900 --> 20:03.367
I just look at
photos of fetuses

20:03.400 --> 20:04.799
and think, how can
we flush them

20:04.830 --> 20:06.320
down the drain?
DAVID:
No one's flushing anything

20:06.370 --> 20:07.735
down the drain.

20:07.770 --> 20:09.863
I met this Rockette
back the '505.

20:09.900 --> 20:12.300
Looked just like Cyd Charisse.

20:12.340 --> 20:13.898
Oh, God, Cyd Charisse!

20:13.940 --> 20:15.874
Those legs! Oh!
WALLIS:
If men could get pregnant,

20:15.910 --> 20:17.844
abortion would be
a sacrament.
HECT: It's legal.

20:17.880 --> 20:19.643
What else do you want?
We were messing around,

20:19.680 --> 20:21.511
you know, backstage,
the green room.

20:21.550 --> 20:23.984
She came to me
three months later, pregnant.

20:24.020 --> 20:25.908
Are you
kidding me?!

20:25.950 --> 20:27.850
Took her to Canada.

20:27.890 --> 20:29.289
HECT: This is what
I don't get about abortion.

20:29.320 --> 20:32.426
Where do you think
the personality went.
If it had been aborted...

20:32.460 --> 20:33.927
(all talking at once)

20:33.960 --> 20:35.723
Hold on. Hold on!

20:35.760 --> 20:36.692
Quiet down.

20:36.730 --> 20:38.960
We're here to negotiate
Diane's exit package.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.160
DAVID: And I have
some research.

20:40.200 --> 20:43.328
This is what we offered Jonas
Stern when he exited in 2009.

20:43.370 --> 20:45.509
Are you friggin' kidding me?
We were in better

20:45.540 --> 20:46.529
financial straits back then.

20:46.570 --> 20:47.878
We should offer
her half of this

20:47.910 --> 20:49.878
and she'd still
be lucky.
I don't disagree.

20:49.910 --> 20:51.775
Jonas Stern was

20:51.810 --> 20:53.448
a founding partner...
So is Diane.

20:53.480 --> 20:54.947
So was Diane.
She's leaving.

20:54.980 --> 20:56.948
There's no difference
between Jonas's impact

20:56.980 --> 20:58.538
on the firm and Diane's.
DAVID:
That may have

20:58.590 --> 21:00.854
been true back then,
but the firm has changed.

21:00.890 --> 21:02.357
What has Diane done but move us

21:02.390 --> 21:04.881
toward bankruptcy?
David, she's going to be

21:04.930 --> 21:07.023
a Supreme Court justice.
WILL: I agree
with Alicia.

21:07.060 --> 21:09.858
Here's the other problem--
Diane has good clients.

21:09.900 --> 21:11.822
We anger her with
a lowball offer, we lose them.

21:11.870 --> 21:13.337
DAVID: How will
we lose them?

21:13.370 --> 21:15.361
She suggests
they go somewhere else.

21:15.400 --> 21:16.936
Let's be practical.

21:16.970 --> 21:22.806
We offer a fair amount;
we keep her clients with us.

21:22.840 --> 21:26.003
Tara's fetus won't be viable
until the third trimester.

21:26.050 --> 21:27.870
And that's in 48 hours?

21:27.920 --> 21:30.445
Yes, that's why the
decision to terminate

21:30.490 --> 21:31.718
has to be made quickly.

21:31.750 --> 21:35.914
Now, Tara's ob-gyn has suggested
that the fetus is viable now.

21:35.960 --> 21:37.450
Yes, I heard that.
She's wrong.

21:37.490 --> 21:39.026
Viability is based
on survivability

21:39.060 --> 21:40.550
outside Tara's womb.

21:40.600 --> 21:42.022
And that's why the Supreme Court

21:42.060 --> 21:44.927
in Roe v. Wade established
the beginning of
the third trimester

21:44.970 --> 21:47.393
as an inviolable line?
Yes, exactly.

21:47.440 --> 21:48.930
Thank you, Doctor.

21:48.970 --> 21:50.961
Nothing further.

21:52.870 --> 21:56.431
Dr. Tuft, isn't survivability
based on current technology?

21:56.480 --> 21:58.869
Of course.
And given the
current improvements

21:58.910 --> 22:00.946
in postnatal technology,

22:00.980 --> 22:03.949
can't the fetus survive_
out5ide Tara's womb earlier?

22:03.990 --> 22:05.082
Not in my opinion, no.

22:05.120 --> 22:06.883
This is a very
special case.

22:06.920 --> 22:09.559
Doctor, don't you have a reason
for wanting the fetus aborted?

22:09.590 --> 22:10.659
SCHMIDT:
Excuse me, objection,
Your Honor.

22:10.690 --> 22:12.123
Who's questioning the witness?

22:12.160 --> 22:14.424
If the fetus is aborted,
then the malpractice lawsuit

22:14.460 --> 22:16.394
against you will be reduced.
Objection, Your Honor!

22:16.430 --> 22:18.523
The defense is turning this into
an argument about malpractice.

22:18.570 --> 22:20.197
No, no, no, you don't have...
We all know you're excited
to be in big boy court.

22:20.230 --> 22:22.892
If you have a problem with me...
You might want to check
the laws on slander, sir.

22:22.940 --> 22:25.761
I'm not slandering the witness,
I'm asking him a...
You're saying...

22:27.010 --> 22:29.570
JUDGE:
The question before me

22:29.610 --> 22:31.999
is whether this contract
is moot.

22:32.050 --> 22:33.972
Due to fetal viability,

22:34.020 --> 22:36.011
there's no way
not to be in breach.

22:36.050 --> 22:38.644
Given the conflicting testimony
of the doctors,

22:38.690 --> 22:40.419
I have no way to split this...

22:40.460 --> 22:42.155
uh, dilemma.

22:42.190 --> 22:45.387
So I fall back on the
Supreme Court's deCI5ion.

22:45.430 --> 22:46.749
Damn it.

22:46.790 --> 22:49.395
JUDGE:
With respect to the contract
in question,

22:49.430 --> 22:51.967
the fetus is ruled nonviable

22:52.000 --> 22:54.389
and will remain so
for 40 more hours.
Your Honor?

22:54.440 --> 22:57.068
Given that, we move that these
proceedings continue apace.

22:57.100 --> 22:59.102
Uh, Your Honor, we don't have
our next witness until Friday.

22:59.140 --> 23:00.573
Mrs. Florrick.

23:00.610 --> 23:02.931
Have your witnesses
available this afternoon.

23:02.980 --> 23:04.868
Or we will proceed
without them.

23:04.910 --> 23:06.377
(gavelbangs)

23:08.680 --> 23:10.910
No.

23:10.950 --> 23:12.110
HOWARD:
What does that mean?

23:12.150 --> 23:15.119
It means I don't accept
your exit package.

23:15.160 --> 23:17.685
We can shove you out,
you know.

23:17.730 --> 23:18.924
Yes, I do know that.

23:18.960 --> 23:21.520
And my clients, too.

23:21.560 --> 23:22.788
What is that-- a threat?

23:22.830 --> 23:23.967
It is a fact.

23:24.000 --> 23:25.865
Don't act innocent.

23:25.900 --> 23:28.164
You already have some of the
associates calling my clients,

23:28.200 --> 23:31.101
trying to split them off.

23:31.140 --> 23:32.232
You're paranoid, Diane.

23:34.580 --> 23:36.002
And I am not Jonas Stern.

23:38.850 --> 23:39.805
What do you want, Diane?

23:39.850 --> 23:41.841
I want what I'm worth.

23:41.880 --> 23:44.019
You want me to not bad
talk you to my clients,

23:44.050 --> 23:45.142
rethink your offer.

23:45.190 --> 23:48.011
Now get out of my office.

23:48.060 --> 23:49.755
This isn't your office.

23:49.790 --> 23:50.859
It is.

23:50.890 --> 23:53.029
Until you have the security
guards escort me out.

23:58.230 --> 24:00.164
Alicia?

24:00.200 --> 24:01.189
Do you have a minute?

24:01.240 --> 24:03.435
I... Sure.

24:06.610 --> 24:08.874
I can't decide this by myself.

24:08.910 --> 24:11.071
But I can sway
most of the partners.

24:11.110 --> 24:12.998
And I think you'll enjoy
a honeymoon period

24:13.050 --> 24:14.119
as the governor's wife.

24:14.150 --> 24:16.846
Oh... okay.
I'm not...

24:16.880 --> 24:20.111
I want you to consider replacing
Diane as managing partner.

24:29.260 --> 24:32.058
Tara asked a lot of questions
about the contract.

24:32.100 --> 24:34.489
We listened, made changes
at her request.

24:34.540 --> 24:37.100
We wanted her
to feel part of the process.

24:37.140 --> 24:38.937
SCHMIDT:
And who represented Ms. Bach?

24:38.970 --> 24:40.232
Alicia Florrick.
I see.

24:40.270 --> 24:43.740
And did Mrs. Florrick
ever raise any concerns

24:43.780 --> 24:46.248
that the surrogacy contract
was coercive in any way?

24:46.280 --> 24:48.612
Your Honor,
respondent would stipulate

24:48.650 --> 24:50.811
that the contract _
as a whole is not coerCIve.

24:50.850 --> 24:53.216
This is about
a Single prOVI5ion.
Yes.

24:53.250 --> 24:54.649
Now that Mrs. Florrick
has given herself cover

24:54.690 --> 24:55.657
against a malpractice suit,

24:55.690 --> 24:57.282
may I continue?

24:57.320 --> 25:00.084
The provision regarding
your right

25:00.130 --> 25:01.722
to terminate the pregnancy,

25:01.760 --> 25:04.069
that wasn't part
of the standard agency contract.

25:04.100 --> 25:05.260
Was it?
No.

25:05.300 --> 25:06.267
My husband and I insisted on it.

25:06.300 --> 25:08.734
Why?

25:08.770 --> 25:11.603
Because our first child, Caleb,
had a heart defect.

25:11.640 --> 25:13.198
He lived six months.

25:13.240 --> 25:15.174
Five operations.

25:15.210 --> 25:16.370
And in the end, we just...

25:16.410 --> 25:19.208
we couldn't bring another
child into the world to suffer.

25:19.250 --> 25:21.969
And is that why you want
to terminate this pregnancy?

25:23.920 --> 25:25.911
Yes.

25:28.020 --> 25:30.727
I wish I were the one
that were pregnant.

25:30.760 --> 25:34.548
But I'm not.

25:34.600 --> 25:36.852
But it's our child.

25:36.900 --> 25:38.162
Our choice.

25:39.330 --> 25:42.197
No one should be allowed
to take that from us.

25:42.240 --> 25:43.707
PETER:
What I want

25:43.740 --> 25:45.332
is a proposed budget
before the state assembly...

25:45.370 --> 25:48.237
So, Barry Rovinski's company
owns the building

25:48.280 --> 25:51.704
that Alicia's new fi_rm
just leased space in?

25:51.750 --> 25:55.277
Yes, an obvious
conflict of interest.

25:55.320 --> 25:58.016
I assure you neither
Peter nor Alicia knew that

25:58.050 --> 26:00.280
when he appointed Barry
to the water board.

26:00.320 --> 26:01.355
Yes, but the terms of
the lease might be

26:01.390 --> 26:02.948
considered preferential.

26:02.990 --> 26:04.958
25 a square foot in an area

26:04.990 --> 26:07.049
where 40's the market rate?

26:07.090 --> 26:08.728
What would you
have Peter do?

26:08.760 --> 26:10.227
The lease has already
been executed.

26:10.260 --> 26:12.194
I think he should reconsider

26:12.230 --> 26:14.232
Barry's candidacy.

26:16.240 --> 26:17.639
He'll look into it.

26:19.110 --> 26:21.829
I was promised
unfettered access.

26:21.880 --> 26:23.131
All due respect,

26:23.180 --> 26:24.147
you are not the
governor-elect.

26:24.180 --> 26:25.374
Yes, thank you
for your respect.

26:25.410 --> 26:27.241
And this is unfettered access

26:27.280 --> 26:28.315
to the governor's
chief of staff.

26:29.750 --> 26:31.308
We should be on
the same side, Eli.

26:31.350 --> 26:32.886
We are on the same side.

26:32.920 --> 26:34.319
You can't keep
disagreeing with me

26:34.360 --> 26:35.258
and pretend it's an agreement.

26:35.290 --> 26:37.087
I agree.
(laughs)

26:37.120 --> 26:39.179
Okay.

26:39.230 --> 26:40.993
Ethical issues
are never obVIous

26:41.030 --> 26:42.156
and they never go away.

26:42.200 --> 26:44.191
That's why I raise them.

26:44.230 --> 26:45.868
Because I like Peter and
want to see him succeed.

26:45.900 --> 26:47.162
You mean, Mr. Florrick?

26:48.700 --> 26:50.702
Of course.

26:52.210 --> 26:53.871
ALICIA:
Mrs. Isenstadt,

26:53.910 --> 26:56.902
you believe you and your husband
have absolute autonomy

26:56.940 --> 26:58.043
over the fate of this...

26:58.080 --> 26:59.274
fetus, right?

26:59.310 --> 27:01.210
Yes, I do.

27:01.250 --> 27:03.070
Why is that?

27:03.120 --> 27:04.382
Because it's ours.

27:04.420 --> 27:05.387
And what about your body?

27:05.420 --> 27:06.842
Do you think you should
have control over that?

27:06.890 --> 27:08.152
Over my body?

27:08.190 --> 27:09.259
Yes, I do.

27:09.290 --> 27:10.848
So, you're pro-choice?

27:10.890 --> 27:13.188
Yes, but this is different.

27:13.230 --> 27:15.118
How? How is it different?

27:15.160 --> 27:17.128
You want this contract imposed

27:17.160 --> 27:18.798
even though Tara

27:18.830 --> 27:20.366
doesn't want an abortion.
It's different

27:20.400 --> 27:22.436
because Tara is not the mother.

27:22.470 --> 27:25.064
I'm the mother.
But it's her body.

27:25.110 --> 27:26.759
Objection, argumentative.
It's okay, I...

27:26.810 --> 27:27.777
I want to answer.

27:27.810 --> 27:30.335
Yes, it's her body,

27:30.380 --> 27:33.099
but she has agreed
to subject her body

27:33.150 --> 27:35.414
to my needs as a mother.

27:35.450 --> 27:39.045
The mother--
that's what this contract was.

27:39.090 --> 27:41.957
This is about my choice,
not hers.

27:41.990 --> 27:45.357
So you would drag Tara
to a clinic

27:45.390 --> 27:47.358
and have this fetus

27:47.390 --> 27:49.654
forcibly removed?

27:54.100 --> 27:56.432
Withdrawn.

27:56.470 --> 27:57.664
No more questions.

28:01.110 --> 28:03.704
I'll have a ruling on the
contract's enforceability

28:03.750 --> 28:05.172
within the hour.

28:14.290 --> 28:15.985
(exhales)

28:24.430 --> 28:25.727
(knocking)

28:25.770 --> 28:27.829
Yeah.

28:27.870 --> 28:29.360
Uh, Cary, I have to be
in court in ten minutes.

28:29.400 --> 28:31.402
What do you need?

28:32.540 --> 28:34.337
Are taking
the managing partnership?

28:35.840 --> 28:37.205
Where'd you hear that?

28:37.240 --> 28:38.468
Is it true?

28:41.950 --> 28:43.747
Will offered it to me.

28:43.790 --> 28:45.018
But it's not a sure thing.

28:45.050 --> 28:47.143
And I don't know even
ifI would take it.

28:47.190 --> 28:49.385
But you're considering it?

28:49.420 --> 28:50.785
Don't you think
that would've been

28:50.830 --> 28:51.979
a good thing to tell us?

28:52.030 --> 28:54.055
It just happened.
Alicia.

28:55.560 --> 28:58.358
Staying is a mistake.

28:58.400 --> 29:01.198
You'll always be under Will.

29:04.070 --> 29:06.334
You finally have a chance to get
out from under him, take it.

29:06.370 --> 29:07.871
Managing partnership is not

29:07.910 --> 29:09.935
under_ him.
It is.

29:09.980 --> 29:12.346
Why do you think he's
offering it to you?

29:12.380 --> 29:14.018
He wants_ someone
he can influece.

29:14.050 --> 29:15.347
Someone that he knows.

29:15.380 --> 29:16.369
Okay, thanks, Cary.

29:17.820 --> 29:19.344
Alicia, this is your chance.

29:19.390 --> 29:21.381
Take it.

29:22.420 --> 29:24.388
After much consideration--

29:24.430 --> 29:26.489
actually, 30 minutes
of consideration--

29:26.530 --> 29:29.124
I have concluded that control of
one's body is an absolute.

29:29.160 --> 29:32.027
This principle is enshrined

29:32.070 --> 29:34.459
in our Constitution
and jurisprudence.

29:34.500 --> 29:37.435
Parties may not contract
around it.

29:37.470 --> 29:40.234
A provision empowering
the Isenstadts

29:40.270 --> 29:44.400
to compel an abortion is
an affront to public policy.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.374
The application for
specific performance is denied.

29:47.410 --> 29:49.173
(gavelbangs)
Your Honor, my client

29:49.220 --> 29:50.517
moves _for a
declaratory judgment

29:50.550 --> 29:52.484
that the contract
has been breached.

29:52.520 --> 29:55.011
ALICIA:
Excuse me, Your Honor.

29:55.060 --> 29:58.518
By denying petitioners' motion
for specific performance...
The court has ruled only

29:58.560 --> 30:01.393
that the provision related
to abortion is unenforceable.

30:01.430 --> 30:04.399
Plaintiffs allege a number
of other contractual breaches.
DAVID: What a load

30:04.430 --> 30:07.092
of bunk. They're trying
to extort this lovely
young mother-to-be

30:07.130 --> 30:08.563
into an abortion.
Uh,uh".

30:08.600 --> 30:11.398
(Schmidt and David arguing)

30:11.440 --> 30:12.862
Gentlemen!
(arguing stops)

30:12.910 --> 30:14.468
No!

30:14.510 --> 30:16.501
Mr. Schmidt, what breaches

30:16.540 --> 30:18.041
are you
referring to?

30:18.080 --> 30:20.548
The defendant failed
to live up to various...

30:20.580 --> 30:22.070
performance sections
of the contract.

30:22.120 --> 30:24.338
Oh, come on. Your Honor,
if Mr. Schmidt's clients

30:24.390 --> 30:25.846
wish to bring
a separate suit...

30:25.890 --> 30:28.085
No, no. No need. In the interest

30:28.120 --> 30:30.554
of judicial economy, I will

30:30.590 --> 30:33.889
hear the motion for
declaratory judgment.

30:33.930 --> 30:35.249
(gavelbangs)

30:35.300 --> 30:38.098
They lost, right?
What are they doing now?

30:38.130 --> 30:42.829
DAVID:
Scorching the earth
and poisoning the wells.

30:47.110 --> 30:49.032
(knocking)

30:51.110 --> 30:53.943
Hi, I'm, uh... I'm Cam.

30:53.980 --> 30:57.017
Is Grace here?

30:57.050 --> 30:59.211
She...

30:59.250 --> 31:01.184
Uh, I'm sorry, you're...?

31:01.220 --> 31:03.552
Cam.

31:03.590 --> 31:04.625
You must be Mrs. Florrick.

31:04.660 --> 31:08.118
Uh, I-I told Grace I might
swing by after dinner.

31:08.160 --> 31:10.424
I'm, uh... I'm running
a little late.
She's out.

31:10.460 --> 31:14.430
Um, but maybe you'd like
to come in and have a beer.

31:14.470 --> 31:15.539
Yeah, that'd be great.

31:15.570 --> 31:17.595
Thanks.
Are you insane?

31:17.640 --> 31:19.369
My daughter is
16 years old.

31:19.410 --> 31:22.072
You do not come knocking
at her door again.

31:22.110 --> 31:23.509
Do you understand,
Cam?

31:23.540 --> 31:25.144
Now is the time to say "yes."

31:25.180 --> 31:26.374
Yes.

31:26.410 --> 31:27.968
Good!

31:28.020 --> 31:30.113
Express elevator
is right behind you.

31:30.150 --> 31:31.344
Turn around.

31:35.360 --> 31:38.227
(sighs)

31:40.530 --> 31:43.351
ROBYN:
Why does David Lee
not trust you?

31:43.400 --> 31:46.528
He thinks I'm doing
what you're doing.

31:46.570 --> 31:48.060
What am I doing?

31:48.100 --> 31:49.397
Leaving with Cary

31:49.440 --> 31:51.067
and the other
fourth years.

31:51.110 --> 31:53.931
Oh. Well...
(chuckles)

31:53.980 --> 31:55.936
All right, I need help.

31:55.980 --> 31:57.948
I think this doctor
on the surrogacy case

31:57.980 --> 32:00.005
has a drinking problem,
but I need someone

32:00.050 --> 32:02.678
at the SA's office to
confirm rumors of a DUI.

32:02.720 --> 32:06.178
Do you have
suggestions?
Yes.

32:06.220 --> 32:08.051
Can you tell me them?

32:08.090 --> 32:09.114
No.

32:09.160 --> 32:10.184
Why not?

32:10.220 --> 32:11.721
Robyn, you're leaving.
Yeah.

32:11.760 --> 32:13.182
Well, so is Alicia,
but you help her.

32:16.260 --> 32:20.264
So is Alicia, but you helped
her on the death penalty case.

32:20.300 --> 32:21.733
Alicia's leaving?

32:21.770 --> 32:24.136
Yeah, I thought you knew.

32:26.610 --> 32:28.134
What...

32:31.410 --> 32:33.173
She didn't say anything.

32:33.210 --> 32:34.177
Yeah.

32:34.220 --> 32:36.040
It's supposed to be a secret.

32:36.080 --> 32:37.513
(chuckles)

32:38.550 --> 32:41.155
Check with the clinic's
medical rep.

32:41.190 --> 32:43.454
They usually know
all the doctor's problems.

32:43.490 --> 32:46.323
Thank you.

32:48.400 --> 32:50.595
PETER:
So, Eli tells me

32:50.630 --> 32:53.599
you have a-a concern over
my choice for the water board.

32:53.630 --> 32:56.428
I do. The problem is, sir,
one of appearances.

32:56.470 --> 32:57.767
Appearances. Uh-huh.

32:57.800 --> 32:59.131
So who would you choose?

32:59.170 --> 33:00.603
The current water board head.

33:00.640 --> 33:01.709
Gra bowski?

33:01.740 --> 33:03.401
He's an idiot.
(chuckles)

33:03.440 --> 33:05.078
Well, I can't speak
to that, sir.

33:05.110 --> 33:06.441
Continuity, of course,
is to be valued.

33:06.480 --> 33:09.074
And there would be no hint
of a conflict of interest.

33:09.120 --> 33:10.473
Yes. So what you're saying

33:10.520 --> 33:12.488
is that you would hire
someone second-rate

33:12.520 --> 33:13.748
because they're more ethical?

33:13.790 --> 33:14.814
No, I'm just saying

33:14.860 --> 33:17.488
that a conflict of interest
is a matter of law,

33:17.520 --> 33:19.124
_ and second-rate
is a matter of opinion.

33:19.160 --> 33:20.354
Hmm.

33:20.390 --> 33:22.392
Who do you like better,
Hemingway or Dan Brown?

33:22.430 --> 33:25.024
I'm not a good judge
of literature, sir.

33:26.170 --> 33:27.626
Uh, who's Dan Brown?

33:27.670 --> 33:29.069
Da Vinci Code.

33:29.100 --> 33:30.260
Ah.

33:30.300 --> 33:31.403
Oh, okay.

33:31.440 --> 33:32.702
Well, I haven't read it;
I-I've seen it.

33:32.740 --> 33:34.503
And I really like Tom Hanks.

33:34.540 --> 33:37.134
Who doesn't?

33:39.110 --> 33:42.113
Um, well, I don't think I can
take your advice, Marilyn.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.789
And I really do appreciate
it, but I just...

33:44.820 --> 33:47.243
can't choose Dan Brown
over Hemingway.

33:47.290 --> 33:49.417
Well, thank you
for listening to me, sir.

33:49.460 --> 33:50.813
Sure.

33:50.860 --> 33:54.091
And I'll make sure
I take a look at Da Vinci Code.

33:54.130 --> 33:56.155
(laughing):
Oh, don't do it
on my account.

33:56.200 --> 33:57.451
No.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.297
I spent too many years
in law school

33:59.330 --> 34:01.298
with my eyes glued
to LexisNexis.

34:01.340 --> 34:04.503
I should... uh, probably
broaden my horizons.

34:13.880 --> 34:15.518
Yes, I read the contract.

34:15.550 --> 34:18.713
Could you please read
the highlighted provision?

34:18.750 --> 34:20.479
"During the course
of the pregnancy,

34:20.520 --> 34:21.384
"the surrogate agrees

34:21.420 --> 34:23.411
"not to engage in
any sexual activity

34:23.460 --> 34:26.122
that would constitute
a risk to the fetus."

34:26.160 --> 34:27.559
SCHMIDT:
How many sexual partners

34:27.590 --> 34:29.353
have you had since
your pregnancy?

34:29.400 --> 34:30.753
Four, I guess.

34:30.800 --> 34:32.199
But they always
used a condom.

34:32.230 --> 34:33.424
SCHMIDT:
And did you and any

34:33.470 --> 34:34.835
of these upstanding gentlemen

34:34.870 --> 34:36.531
ever engage in a threesome?

34:36.570 --> 34:37.594
ALICIA:
Objection, Your Honor.

34:37.640 --> 34:38.732
This is character assassination.

34:38.770 --> 34:40.203
SCHMIDT:
An orgy is a

34:40.240 --> 34:42.572
per se violation
of her contractual commitment

34:42.610 --> 34:43.838
not to engage
in rislq

34:43.880 --> 34:45.677
sexual behavior.
