Yes.

35:05.530 --> 35:07.122
Okay, that's a lie.
You're a liar.

35:07.170 --> 35:08.569
I haven't seen you in a year.

35:08.600 --> 35:09.498
JUDGE:
Mrs. Florrick,

35:09.540 --> 35:11.531
if your client can't
restrain herself...

35:11.570 --> 35:14.573
I'm sorry, Your Honor.
It won't happen again.

35:16.340 --> 35:18.547
And what happened
after you brought Evan back?

35:18.580 --> 35:19.706
Well, we double...

35:23.280 --> 35:24.645
I mean, we had a threesome.

35:24.690 --> 35:26.544
SCHMIDT:
And did anyone
use protection?

35:26.590 --> 35:28.512
MAN:
Uh, no. None of us.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.585
DAVID:
It doesn't matter
if he was lying.

35:30.620 --> 35:31.757
The judge believed him.

35:31.790 --> 35:33.280
So, what do we...

35:33.330 --> 35:34.422
(clamoring)

35:34.460 --> 35:36.428
What is going on?

35:36.460 --> 35:37.324
Hello.

35:37.360 --> 35:40.261
Mr. Florrick, it is
so good to meet you.

35:40.300 --> 35:42.461
I'm David Lee, one of
your earlier fans.

35:42.500 --> 35:43.592
Alicia and I
work together.

35:43.640 --> 35:45.232
Oh, hello, Mr. Lee.
How are you?

35:45.270 --> 35:46.430
Good, good.

35:46.470 --> 35:47.539
You have quite
a wife here.

35:47.570 --> 35:48.639
(chuckles)

35:48.680 --> 35:49.874
What's up, Peter?

35:49.910 --> 35:51.502
Nothing. I, uh...
I had a break.

35:51.550 --> 35:52.539
I thought I'd
come say hello.

35:52.580 --> 35:54.241
It was supposed
to be a surprise.

35:54.280 --> 35:55.713
A little difficult
with the security detail.

35:55.750 --> 35:57.615
It's_ still a
surprise to us.

35:57.650 --> 35:58.742
Yeah.

35:58.790 --> 36:00.644
Um, okay, excuse me.

36:00.690 --> 36:03.250
(quietly):
Um, I booked a suite in Wailea.

36:03.290 --> 36:05.429
They have a package
for renewing your vows.

36:06.760 --> 36:08.751
Um, Peter, I thought you said...

36:08.800 --> 36:11.496
I mean, I thought we had to wait
until after the inauguration.

36:11.530 --> 36:13.498
I thought we did, too,
but it will be

36:13.530 --> 36:14.792
just as difficult
after the inauguration,

36:14.840 --> 36:16.592
so I think we should do it now.

36:16.640 --> 36:18.631
What's going on?

36:19.840 --> 36:21.569
Nothing's going on.

36:21.610 --> 36:22.929
I love you.

36:23.980 --> 36:25.607
I love you, too. I...

36:25.650 --> 36:26.901
I'm sorry to bother you,
Mr. Florrick.

36:26.950 --> 36:28.508
Alicia, the judge
wants us back in.

36:28.550 --> 36:30.211
(sighs)

36:30.250 --> 36:31.615
Your Honor,
30 minutes ago,

36:31.650 --> 36:33.538
Ms. Bach approached
my client and offered

36:33.590 --> 36:34.989
to abort the fetus
for $100,000.

36:35.020 --> 36:37.284
DAVID: _
Judge, that is a
preposterous lie.

36:37.320 --> 36:38.651
It constitutes
blackmail, Your Honor.

36:38.690 --> 36:39.588
Wait a minute.

36:39.630 --> 36:41.621
Yo_u've ruled _
that my client has the right

36:41.660 --> 36:43.491
to decide whether
to have an abortion.

36:43.530 --> 36:45.521
There's nothing illegal
about monetizing that right.

36:45.570 --> 36:48.289
So you're saying
that she made this offer?

36:48.340 --> 36:50.262
No, I'm saying,
if she did make this offer--

36:50.300 --> 36:51.858
and I have no knowledge
that she did--

36:51.910 --> 36:54.333
she was merely using money
as a carrot,

36:54.380 --> 36:55.836
just as the Isenstadts
used it as a stick.

36:55.880 --> 36:57.370
Judge, if tying

36:57.410 --> 36:58.707
the destruction of a fetus

36:58.750 --> 37:00.570
to the payment of money
isn't blackmail, nothing is.

37:00.610 --> 37:02.612
JUDGE:
Okay. I'll hear
from Ms. Bach

37:02.650 --> 37:03.947
on this question
first thing tomorrow.

37:03.980 --> 37:06.414
ALICIA:
Judge, even if she
were to make the offer,

37:06.450 --> 37:07.348
it was nothing more

37:07.390 --> 37:09.415
than a permissible
settlement negotiation

37:09.460 --> 37:10.882
in a civil_case.
Or a crime.

37:10.920 --> 37:12.820
If I find your client's
committed one,

37:12.860 --> 37:14.555
I'll refer her to the
state's attorney.

37:21.300 --> 37:24.963
Mom, did you tell Cam
to leave me alone?

37:25.010 --> 37:26.966
Good morning, Grace.

37:27.010 --> 37:28.602
Did you tell Cam
to get lost?

37:28.640 --> 37:31.029
_ You mean the man
With the motorcycle helmet,

37:31.080 --> 37:33.708
the man who came to my door,
who wanted to come in

37:33.750 --> 37:34.876
and have a beer
and wait for you?

37:34.920 --> 37:36.512
Mom, he's my pastor.

37:37.550 --> 37:40.280
He's the head
of Campus Faith.

37:40.320 --> 37:42.288
He was supposed to pick
up some reading plans.

37:43.320 --> 37:47.051
Okay... Grace,
he didn't look like a...

37:47.090 --> 37:48.751
I don't know what
he looked like,

37:48.800 --> 37:51.360
but just because
they're pastors

37:51.400 --> 37:53.891
doesn't mean anything.

37:54.900 --> 37:57.039
Mom, what's going on?

37:59.070 --> 38:01.800
I saw the Web site--
the ten hottest daughters.

38:01.840 --> 38:03.933
Zach showed you.
No, I forced him
to show me.

38:03.980 --> 38:07.040
Mom, that doesn't
mean anything.

38:07.080 --> 38:08.342
I'm not after all of that.

38:08.380 --> 38:10.473
I know, honey,
but boys are.

38:10.520 --> 38:12.385
So?
So...

38:12.420 --> 38:14.615
you're dressing
differently.

38:14.660 --> 38:16.514
You're taking dresses
from my closet.

38:16.560 --> 38:17.481
You said I could.

38:17.520 --> 38:20.023
I know, but, Grace,
I'm your mom, and this...

38:20.060 --> 38:24.497
Mom... I want
to be pretty.

38:27.770 --> 38:30.933
Just let me be pretty.

38:30.970 --> 38:34.428
Oh, honey,
you a pretty.

38:34.480 --> 38:36.471
No, you have
to say that.

38:39.150 --> 38:42.039
I want other people to
think that I'm pretty.

38:50.090 --> 38:52.786
Did you tell my clients
that you'd only have an abortion

38:52.830 --> 38:55.048
if they paid you $100,000?

38:55.100 --> 38:57.091
No, I did not.
If the court
would please instruct

38:57.130 --> 38:58.051
the witness
she's under oath...

38:58.100 --> 38:59.727
Objection, Your Honor.

38:59.770 --> 39:02.432
The witness has been sworn
and is fully aware of that.

39:03.470 --> 39:05.631
You are under oath,

39:05.670 --> 39:06.762
ma'am.
(gasps)

39:07.610 --> 39:08.531
RO BYN :
Psst.

39:08.580 --> 39:11.378
TARA:
I might have said
that $100,000...

39:11.410 --> 39:13.947
I was looking
into the possibility

39:13.980 --> 39:15.140
that Dr. Tuft has a DUI.

39:15.180 --> 39:16.647
Really?
Yeah.

39:16.680 --> 39:18.819
He doesn't, but I was checking
with his medical reps

39:18.850 --> 39:20.738
and I did find out
something else.

39:22.120 --> 39:24.429
SCHMIDT:
So, what do you have?

39:24.460 --> 39:27.452
DAVID:
As Dr. Tuft's notes show,
he cultured the embryo

39:27.490 --> 39:29.492
48 hours prior
to implantation.

39:29.530 --> 39:31.521
Meaning there's been
a miscalculation of fetal age.

39:31.570 --> 39:32.923
Let me see that.

39:32.970 --> 39:35.029
We're in the third trimester,
Mr. Schmidt,

39:35.070 --> 39:38.437
meaning the
fetus is viable.

39:38.470 --> 39:39.801
DAVID:
Which means you won't
be able to pressure

39:39.840 --> 39:41.831
our client
to terminate.

39:43.440 --> 39:45.442
Okay.

39:51.690 --> 39:53.646
You're selfish, Tara.

39:53.690 --> 39:56.682
It'd be one thing
if you said I'm adopting him,

39:56.720 --> 39:59.188
but you're walking away.

39:59.230 --> 40:02.495
Remember what you said, Kathy,
after the first sonogram?

40:02.530 --> 40:05.169
"Do everything you can
to protect my baby."

40:05.200 --> 40:06.827
(scoffs)
This isn't protecting.

40:06.870 --> 40:08.064
It's owning.

40:08.100 --> 40:09.499
I'm keeping him alive.

40:09.540 --> 40:12.134
That's the only way I
know how to protect him.

40:12.170 --> 40:14.536
Feel him
kicking, Kathy.

40:14.580 --> 40:16.798
Just feel him.

40:22.180 --> 40:24.171
No.

40:34.230 --> 40:36.824
DAVID:
It's the final offer, Diane.

40:36.860 --> 40:39.021
No, it's the final offer
when I accept it.

40:43.970 --> 40:45.733
No.

40:45.770 --> 40:48.534
Howard, David, could you
please give us a moment?

40:48.580 --> 40:49.535
HOWARD:
We got a problem?

40:49.580 --> 40:52.708
No, just something
between Diane and myself.

40:53.880 --> 40:55.848
Alicia, you stay.

40:55.880 --> 40:58.542
I'm going to want you to run
a change in the contract.

41:03.290 --> 41:05.485
What do you want?

41:05.530 --> 41:06.485
More than this.

41:06.530 --> 41:09.249
No, this isn't about money.

41:09.300 --> 41:10.756
This is about us.

41:10.800 --> 41:12.791
So, what do you want
from me?

41:16.600 --> 41:19.160
I put my life
into this place.

41:20.170 --> 41:21.137
My whole life.

41:21.170 --> 41:22.137
And it's appreciated.

41:22.180 --> 41:23.204
No, it's not--

41:23.240 --> 41:26.004
not with ghouls like that
shoving me out the door.

41:26.050 --> 41:27.745
Well, I can't negotiate
appreciation.

41:27.780 --> 41:29.042
That's right.

41:29.080 --> 41:32.117
That's why you'd better do it
with money.

41:38.260 --> 41:42.128
And how much appreciation are
you looking for, Your Honor?

41:47.930 --> 41:50.694
I must have really hurt you...

41:50.740 --> 41:52.560
to make you want
to hurt me like this.

41:52.610 --> 41:55.272
That was the deal from the
beginning, Diane, remember?

41:56.710 --> 41:59.008
We work together until it's
not fun or profitable

41:59.050 --> 42:00.574
anymore.

42:00.610 --> 42:02.248
Well, here we are.

42:02.280 --> 42:04.589
Are you having fun?

42:08.960 --> 42:12.259
Bump the package up
by 20% and I'll leave.

42:12.290 --> 42:13.621
I can't do that.

42:13.660 --> 42:14.729
Then find another way.

42:14.760 --> 42:16.751
I'll be at home.

42:23.840 --> 42:25.808
(sighs)

42:25.840 --> 42:26.909
She'll come around.

42:26.940 --> 42:29.306
She knows

42:29.340 --> 42:31.171
_she can't be sworn in
With a partnership dispute

42:31.210 --> 42:32.302
hanging over her head.

42:46.790 --> 42:48.792
We need to leave this week.

42:51.200 --> 42:53.168
You're sure?

42:54.200 --> 42:54.268
Yes.
